						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Siddhanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikramachōḷa Year 6: 1123-24 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may be assigned to about the 12th century A.D., on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>The record registers the gift of one <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> deposited into the temple treasury for providing a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the deity by Sūriyadēvan of Panaṅguḍi in Paṉaiyūr-nāḍu in Kōlōttuṅgaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. The lamp was to be maintained from the <hi rend="italic">vṛiddhi</hi> accured from out of one <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> endowed.</p>						

						</summary>
